Explore Predictions for Multiclass Outcomes

Multiclass classification models predict probable outcomes for 3â€“10 categories. A prediction selects the class with the highest probability of winning based on the values of predictor variables.

To simulate and explore future outcomes:

Open a Model that is associated with a multiclass classification use case.
On the Model Toolbar, click Predictions.
The screen provides selectors in the left panel.
Under Select a Group to Predict, select an option from one or more features. The right panel shows the predicted results.

Einstein Prediction: prediction score for your selections
Ranked List: chart that shows the predicted probabilities of each class
Model Accuracy: chart that shows the accuracy of the model as applied to the training dataset
Top Prediction Factors: explanatory variables, favorable and unfavorable, that are most strongly associated with the predicted outcome
Predicted Outcome: chart that shows how the top predictors influenced the predicted outcome
